# Dialog

The Dialog component provides a modal dialog with backdrop, customizable sizes, and full accessibility support including focus trapping and keyboard navigation.

## Examples

### Basic Dialog

<div style="margin: var(--lt-spacing-4) 0;">
  <lt-button id="open-basic-dialog" variant="primary">Open Dialog</lt-button>
</div>

<lt-dialog id="basic-dialog" title="Welcome">
  <p>This is a basic dialog with default settings.</p>
  <div slot="footer">
    <lt-button id="close-basic-dialog" variant="primary">OK</lt-button>
  </div>
</lt-dialog>

```html
<lt-button id="open-dialog">Open Dialog</lt-button>

<lt-dialog id="my-dialog" title="Welcome">
  <p>Dialog content here</p>
  <div slot="footer">
    <lt-button id="close-dialog">OK</lt-button>
  </div>
</lt-dialog>

<script>
  document.getElementById('open-dialog').addEventListener('click', () => {
    document.getElementById('my-dialog').show();
  });
  document.getElementById('close-dialog').addEventListener('click', () => {
    document.getElementById('my-dialog').hide();
  });
</script>
```

### Dialog Sizes

<div style="display: flex; gap: var(--lt-spacing-3); margin: var(--lt-spacing-4) 0; flex-wrap: wrap;">
  <lt-button id="open-sm-dialog" variant="secondary">Small</lt-button>
  <lt-button id="open-md-dialog" variant="secondary">Medium</lt-button>
  <lt-button id="open-lg-dialog" variant="secondary">Large</lt-button>
  <lt-button id="open-xl-dialog" variant="secondary">Extra Large</lt-button>
  <lt-button id="open-fullscreen-dialog" variant="secondary">Fullscreen</lt-button>
</div>

<lt-dialog id="sm-dialog" title="Small Dialog" size="sm">
  <p>This is a small dialog.</p>
  <div slot="footer">
    <lt-button id="close-sm-dialog">Close</lt-button>
  </div>
</lt-dialog>

<lt-dialog id="md-dialog" title="Medium Dialog" size="md">
  <p>This is a medium dialog (default size).</p>
  <div slot="footer">
    <lt-button id="close-md-dialog">Close</lt-button>
  </div>
</lt-dialog>

<lt-dialog id="lg-dialog" title="Large Dialog" size="lg">
  <p>This is a large dialog with more content space.</p>
  <div slot="footer">
    <lt-button id="close-lg-dialog">Close</lt-button>
  </div>
</lt-dialog>

<lt-dialog id="xl-dialog" title="Extra Large Dialog" size="xl">
  <p>This is an extra large dialog.</p>
  <div slot="footer">
    <lt-button id="close-xl-dialog">Close</lt-button>
  </div>
</lt-dialog>

<lt-dialog id="fullscreen-dialog" title="Fullscreen Dialog" size="fullscreen">
  <p>This dialog takes up the entire viewport.</p>
  <div slot="footer">
    <lt-button id="close-fullscreen-dialog">Close</lt-button>
  </div>
</lt-dialog>

```html
<lt-dialog size="sm">Small</lt-dialog>
<lt-dialog size="md">Medium (default)</lt-dialog>
<lt-dialog size="lg">Large</lt-dialog>
<lt-dialog size="xl">Extra Large</lt-dialog>
<lt-dialog size="fullscreen">Fullscreen</lt-dialog>
```

### Form Dialog

<div style="margin: var(--lt-spacing-4) 0;">
  <lt-button id="open-form-dialog" variant="primary">Open Form</lt-button>
</div>

<lt-dialog id="form-dialog" title="User Information">
  <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--lt-spacing-4);">
    <lt-textfield label="Name" required></lt-textfield>
    <lt-textfield label="Email" type="email" required></lt-textfield>
    <lt-textfield label="Message" multiline rows="4"></lt-textfield>
  </div>
  <div slot="footer" style="display: flex; gap: var(--lt-spacing-3); justify-content: flex-end;">
    <lt-button id="cancel-form" variant="secondary">Cancel</lt-button>
    <lt-button id="submit-form" variant="primary">Submit</lt-button>
  </div>
</lt-dialog>

## Properties

| Property | Type | Default | Description |
|----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `open` | `boolean` | `false` | Controls dialog visibility |
| `title` | `string` | `''` | Dialog title |
| `size` | `'sm' \| 'md' \| 'lg' \| 'xl' \| 'fullscreen'` | `'md'` | Dialog size |
| `hide-close-button` | `boolean` | `false` | Hides the close button |
| `close-on-backdrop-click` | `boolean` | `true` | Close when clicking backdrop |
| `close-on-escape` | `boolean` | `true` | Close when pressing Escape |

## Methods

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `show()` | Opens the dialog |
| `hide()` | Closes the dialog |
| `toggle()` | Toggles dialog visibility |

## Events

| Event | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `lt-open` | Fired when dialog opens |
| `lt-close` | Fired when dialog closes |

## Slots

| Slot | Description |
|------|-------------|
| (default) | Dialog content |
| `footer` | Dialog footer (typically for action buttons) |

## Accessibility

- Focus trap keeps focus within dialog
- Escape key closes dialog (configurable)
- Backdrop click closes dialog (configurable)
- Body scroll is prevented when open
- Proper ARIA attributes (`role="dialog"`, `aria-modal="true"`)
- Focus is returned to trigger element on close

<script is:inline type="module">
  import '@latty/web';

  // Basic dialog
  const openBasic = document.getElementById('open-basic-dialog');
  const closeBasic = document.getElementById('close-basic-dialog');
  const basicDialog = document.getElementById('basic-dialog');
  
  if (openBasic && basicDialog) {
    openBasic.addEventListener('click', () => basicDialog.show());
  }
  if (closeBasic && basicDialog) {
    closeBasic.addEventListener('click', () => basicDialog.hide());
  }

  // Size dialogs
  const sizes = ['sm', 'md', 'lg', 'xl', 'fullscreen'];
  sizes.forEach(size => {
    const openBtn = document.getElementById(`open-${size}-dialog`);
    const closeBtn = document.getElementById(`close-${size}-dialog`);
    const dialog = document.getElementById(`${size}-dialog`);
    
    if (openBtn && dialog) {
      openBtn.addEventListener('click', () => dialog.show());
    }
    if (closeBtn && dialog) {
      closeBtn.addEventListener('click', () => dialog.hide());
    }
  });

  // Form dialog
  const openForm = document.getElementById('open-form-dialog');
  const cancelForm = document.getElementById('cancel-form');
  const submitForm = document.getElementById('submit-form');
  const formDialog = document.getElementById('form-dialog');
  
  if (openForm && formDialog) {
    openForm.addEventListener('click', () => formDialog.show());
  }
  if (cancelForm && formDialog) {
    cancelForm.addEventListener('click', () => formDialog.hide());
  }
  if (submitForm && formDialog) {
    submitForm.addEventListener('click', () => {
      alert('Form submitted!');
      formDialog.hide();
    });
  }
</script>
